Name: Bill
S18S1V01: That the  Report on the Bill (E2), intituled: An Act to enable the establishment, operation and maintenance of free foreign trade zones by provinces and municipalities or by public agencies of either thereof be now adopted (p.217/405).
S18S1V02: Motion to amend the Address to His Most Excellent Majesty the King, praying that he may graciously be pleased to give his consent to submitting a measure to the Parliament of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland to amend the British North America Acts, 1867 to 1930, and the British North America Act, 1907, as amended (p.239/405).
S18S1V03:
That the Senate do unite with the House of Commons in an Address to His
Most Excellent Majesty the King, praying that he may graciously be pleased to give his consent to submitting a measure to the Parliament of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland to amend the British North America Acts, 1867 to 1930, and the British North America Act, 1907, main motion (p.239/405).
S18S2V01: Third reading of the Bill (B), intituled: An Act to establish a Board of Transport Commissioners for Canada, with authority in respect of transport by railways, ships, aircraft and motor vehicles (p.170/309).
S18S2V02: That the Bill (12), intituled: An Act to provide for revision of the accounting set-up of the Canadian National Railway System, as amended be not now read a third time, but that it be amended by adding the following at the end of Clause 11 (p.233/309).
S18S3V01: Second reading of the Bill (B), intituled: An Act respecting Divorce and Matrimonial Causes (p.88/457).
S18S3V02: Third reading of the Bill (B) intituled: "An Act respecting Divorce and Matrimonial Causes, as amended i.e. that it be read this day six months  (p.134/457).
S18S3V03: Third reading of the Bill (B), intituled: An Act respecting Divorce and Matrimonial Causes, as amended (p.218/457).
S18S3V04: Third reading of the Bill (25), intituled: An Act to amend The Farmers Creditors Arrangement Act, 1934, as amended (p.286/457).
S18S3V05: Third reading of the Bill (31), intituled: An Act to establish a Board of Transport Commissioners for Canada, with authority in respect of transport by railways, ships and aircraft, as amended i.e. that the word now be left out and the words this day six months added at the end of the motion (p.383/457).
S18S3V06: Third reading of the Bill (175), intituled: An Act respecting Penitentiaries (p.390/457).
S18S4V01: Second reading of the Bill (86), intituled: An Act to amend The Farmers Creditors Arrangement Act, 1934 (p.131/385).
S18S4V02: Third reading of the Bill (1-2), intituled: An Act to amend the Canadian National-Canadian Pacific Act, 1933, as amended (p.246/385).
S18S4V03: That the third Report of the Special Committee of the Senate appointed to inquire into and report upon the best means of relieving the country from its extremely serious railway condition and the financial burden appertaining thereto be now adopted (p.296/385).
S18S4V04:
That the said Bill, as amended, be not now read a third time, but that it
be referred beak to the Standing Committee on Banking and Commerce (p.319/385).
S18S4V05: That the Bill (132), intituled: An Act to incorporate the Central Mortgage Bank, as amended, be not now read a third time, but that it be further amended (p.320/385).
